<s> Andrew Clover (http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/www-dom/2003OctDec/0077.h tml) also implemented his Python L&amp;S where parse failures threw IO and similar exceptions.  </s>
<s> The spec doesn't give a huge guideance on the reporting of error conditions, the current scheme of swallowing exceptions and returning null in the Java implementations is compelled by method signature in the Java binding prohibiting throwing checked exceptions other than DOMException.  </s>
<s> Instead of immediately conforming to the other Java implementations, I'd hold off until we address this issue.  </s>
